songs.title: September

description.plain:
In “September,” Maurice White reminisces over a nostalgic period that took place in the month of September.

As a joyful classic, the song has appeared in a variety of commercials and movies, and has even served as the inspiration for a movie title. Interest in the song spikes yearly every September 21, and more recently the subject of celebration on Twitter. The song also inspired the City of Los Angeles to declare that the 21st of September would be Earth, Wind & Fire Day, in honor of the band’s connections to the city.

This 1978 hit became number one on the U.S. R&B chart and reached the eighth position on the Billboard Hot 100. It was written by Maurice White, Al McKay, and Allee Willis.

songs.title: Let’s Groove

description.plain: “Let’s Groove” is the lead single off of Earth, Wind & Fire’s 11th studio album, Raise! It was released in late 1981, and remained on the top charts well into 1982. It reached gold certification in the United States, and silver in the UK. The song reached number three in the top charts of both countries. This was a huge success, considering the hostility felt by many rock and punk fans in the United States towards disco at the time. The track itself is catchy, though some critics regarded it as generic.
